        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 29 at 3:37PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 337 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles south of Abbeville, or near Troy, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bradley, Callison, Troy, Kirksey, and Promised Land.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
